<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="216" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[113,647,1545,1688]" pageId="13" pageNumber="216">
DIAGNOSIS. — 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Minchin" authorityYear="1900" box="[268,424,1613,1637]" class="Calcarea" family="Leucosoleniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leucosolenida" pageId="13" pageNumber="216" phylum="Porifera" rank="family">Leucosoleniidae</taxonomicName>
in which the skeleton can consist of diactines, triactines and/or tetractines. There is no reinforced external layer on the tubes.
</paragraph>
